Apt Utility

Apt is a command-line utility for installing, updating, removing and otherwise managing packages in Ubuntu,
Debian and related Linux distros. Most of the apt commands must be proceeded by sudo.

Syntax:
Installing packages with apt:    
    sudo apt install (package name)(package name)

Removing packages with apt:
    sudo apt remove (package name)

To keep packages up to date:
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt upgrade

To view currently installed packages
    sudo apt list